As disease developed, she grew more ashamed, and re-designed her headdress to cover most of her face.
An opulent dress embellished with gold chains to display her wealth and importance to the goat-horned god.
Inspired by the symbols of the god of water and mischief, from the horned crucible to the goat liver paste inside, this censer carries a nefarious odor.
Passed down through many generations, the headdress is laden with symbolic language.

A used burial shroud styled into priestesses’ robes during the rebirthing ceremony. The former occupant is nothing but dust, stain, and an acrid smell upon the fabric, yet it’s said they protect the wearer from harm.
Filled with tree resin and animal excrement, it's used to purge sickness by causing a heaving, uncontrollable regurgitation.
A shattered headdress resting on a raw, molten scalp.
A once sacred gown torn by the surging power that deformed her body.
Filled with the putrid nectar she drew from glass vials lying around, creating a new nauseating scent.
Her crown of spikes showed her adherence to the dark cult’s most fervent methods, namely impaling the sick.
She bathed in gruesome mixtures of squirming worms, dead flies, and clay. She was desperate to find a cure.
Filled with moist larvae and mushed bee eggs, her censer casted distinct, nauseating fumes.

A crown emanating a festive and ominous aura created by The Entity’s biggest fan.
A headdress that pleases cosmic forces in times of unbalance.
A robe offering fervent devotion to the moon and its role in maintaining light when all else is dark.
A censer made of boulder that fell from the sky, truly a gift from the gods.
The mask of the Maiden Guards represented the executioner, and their divine right to end a sinner's life.
The uniforms of the Maiden Guards showed bare skin, symbolizing the purity of its members—and their right to judge others.
A censer filled with embers and oil, it was used to cleanse a high priest of his blasphemous ways.

A crown crafted for a very special anniversary.
“Thank you for supporting & inspiring us along the years!” —The Dead by Daylight Team
A headdress that represents growth reaching its wondrous apex.
Light fabrics flow gently from the wings of her shoulders.
A warm, inviting glow fills the censer, coyly underplaying the burning heat within.
A deep red headdress that symbolizes vitality and long life.
A robe dyed deep red with the powdered remains of beetles.
The stink of various incenses and reagents emanate from this heavy bronze container.
A vile, cloying scent disperses from the cracks in its glass.
